01:03.008 --> 01:06.803
[Woman] Do you know
the expression ''a man's man'' ?

01:06.886 --> 01:09.972
A man's man
is the leader of the pack.

01:10.056 --> 01:14.977
The kind of man other men
look up to, admire and emulate.

01:16.395 --> 01:18.939
A man's man
is the kind of man who...

01:19.022 --> 01:22.567
[Chuckles] just doesn 't get
what women are about.

01:22.651 --> 01:28.072
Nick, my ex-husband,
is the ultimate man's man.

01:28.156 --> 01:30.074
I probably never
should have married him.

01:30.157 --> 01:32.159
I don't think he understood
a thing about me.

01:32.243 --> 01:35.454
So, this is Nick Marshall's office.
Wanna peek ?

01:35.537 --> 01:37.498
Don't worry.
He never gets in before 10:00.

01:37.539 --> 01:40.375
He'll send you on more errands than
anyone in the entire company...

01:40.459 --> 01:42.377
'cause he can't do
anything for himself.

01:42.460 --> 01:46.381
He's the least politically
correct guy in the universe.

01:46.464 --> 01:48.716
He's the king of all
the T & A ads we do.

01:48.800 --> 01:50.968
You want babes in bikinis ?
He's your man.

01:51.052 --> 01:54.597
My dad ? How can I
best describe him ?

01:54.680 --> 01:57.724
He's always been...
like an uncle to me.

01:57.808 --> 01:59.976
Yeah, Uncle Dad.

02:00.018 --> 02:03.229
Although,
Nick was a charmer.

02:03.313 --> 02:06.482
Completely irresistible
at first,

02:06.524 --> 02:10.318
which feeds into
the whole ''man's man'' thing.

02:10.360 --> 02:13.322
You know about
Nick's mother, right ?

02:13.364 --> 02:17.117
Because once you understand
about Nick's mother,

02:17.201 --> 02:19.494
you understand Nick.

02:22.539 --> 02:27.126
[Woman] Nick was actually
born and raised in Las Vegas.

02:27.210 --> 02:32.256
Nick's mother was a real,
honest-to-God Las Vegas showgirl.

02:32.339 --> 02:37.094
When otherboys were outside
riding their bikes and playing ball,

02:37.177 --> 02:41.515
Nick was backstage
hanging with the girls.

02:41.556 --> 02:45.226
He was their mascot,
their little pet.

02:45.310 --> 02:49.230
They couldn 't get enough
of those baby blues.

02:49.313 --> 02:51.232
- Bang ! Bang !
- [ Laughs ]

02:53.442 --> 02:56.695
lf you ask me, I'd say Nick's
mother just about killed it...

02:56.737 --> 02:59.031
for every woman
Nick would ever meet.

02:59.114 --> 03:02.200
She had a lot of sugardaddies
in her life,

03:02.284 --> 03:05.078
but only one true love--

03:05.161 --> 03:07.914
the boy
with the family jewels.

03:09.290 --> 03:11.959
17, 18, 19, 20.
Let me see that, kid.

03:12.043 --> 03:13.961
And since Nick
didn 't have a father,

03:14.044 --> 03:18.590
his mom made sure he was always
surrounded by strong role models.

03:18.674 --> 03:20.592
- Come here, huh ?
- [ Screams ]

03:20.675 --> 03:23.345
- Men her boy could look up to.
- Now you're ready, huh ?

03:24.929 --> 03:26.848
Keep countin', kid.

03:26.931 --> 03:29.600
There was nothing normal about
the way Nick Marshall was raised.

03:31.102 --> 03:33.687
So, what can you expect ?

03:33.771 --> 03:36.023
You don't have to be Freud
to figure out...

03:36.106 --> 03:39.234
this was one cockeyed way
to enter the world.

04:00.295 --> 04:05.091
[ Groaning ]

04:11.722 --> 04:13.641
Oh !

04:15.309 --> 04:16.810
Don't you ever knock ?

04:18.185 --> 04:20.439
It's almost 10:00. You gotta go
to work, and I gotta vacuum in here.

04:20.522 --> 04:23.274
And don't forget - Another one
who wears vanilla perfume.

04:23.358 --> 04:26.444
Don't you know any women
who don't want to smell like candy ?

04:26.527 --> 04:29.155
- Toss me my lighter, babe ?
- Babe ?

04:29.197 --> 04:31.365
What am I,
a little pig ?

04:31.449 --> 04:33.576
I don't have time
to make you no onion bagel,

04:33.659 --> 04:35.577
so please do not start
to beg, okay ?

04:35.661 --> 04:39.206
And for the record, l don't like
finding these things in your sofa.

04:39.289 --> 04:41.708
What kind of woman
wears underwear like this ?

04:41.750 --> 04:44.044
Hey, my mother wore
underwear like that.

04:44.085 --> 04:46.212
Just put them somewhere,
will you, babe ?

04:46.296 --> 04:49.340
Well, ''babe'' is gonna put it
in the trash where it belongs.

04:49.382 --> 04:51.342
- So, your mother should excuse me.
- [ Sighs ]

04:51.384 --> 04:53.552
Did you ever consider dating
a woman who wears real underwear?

04:53.636 --> 04:57.055
The kind that covers the entire
bottom the way it's supposed to ?

04:57.139 --> 04:59.975
- No. But if I do, should I call ?
- Oh !

05:01.226 --> 05:03.853
I'm gonna go clean
the kitchen.

05:03.895 --> 05:05.855
You couldn't toast me
a little bagel, could you ?

05:05.897 --> 05:08.232
Light cream cheese, tomatoes.
Capers if we have any.

05:08.316 --> 05:11.193
Please! Come on.
l can't think on an empty stomach.

05:11.235 --> 05:14.530
Okay. Allright. But only because
you didn 't call me that pig name.

05:14.571 --> 05:16.573
Okay, you got it, babe.

05:23.246 --> 05:25.665
Mr. Marshall,
how are you doing today ?

05:25.748 --> 05:28.126
- I'm fit as a dancing bear.
- I'll get that cab for you.

05:28.209 --> 05:30.962
- [ Whistles ]
- That's some set of pipes you got.

05:31.045 --> 05:34.882
- You have an excellent day, sir.
- And you.

05:37.509 --> 05:40.345
At ease.

05:54.608 --> 05:57.027
- [ Gasps ]
- Oh, oh, I'm so sorry !

05:57.110 --> 05:58.987
I absolutely
did not mean to do that.

05:59.071 --> 06:00.989
- Here. Let me get that for you.
- It's okay.

06:01.072 --> 06:03.158
No, I'm mortified.
I can see your hands are full.

06:03.241 --> 06:05.451
- Thank you.
- Sorry. Let me get the door.

06:05.535 --> 06:07.453
[ Grunts ]

06:07.537 --> 06:09.455
- [ Giggles ] Thank you.
- Thank you.

06:09.539 --> 06:12.083
Halfcup, grande, nonfat,
thick foam, wet cap, no lid.

06:12.166 --> 06:15.252
''Halfcaff,'' grande, nonfat,
thick foam, wet cap, no lid.

06:15.294 --> 06:17.796
- So, when do you find out ?
- Um, today, I think.

06:17.880 --> 06:22.467
Unless I didn't get it, and then
I will just never find out.

06:22.550 --> 06:24.969
I'm sure I didn't get it. They were
looking for an ''earth mother'' type.

06:25.011 --> 06:27.805
I overheard the director
say I was more space cadet.

06:27.889 --> 06:30.308
I'm an actress.
I can be whatever you want.

06:30.391 --> 06:32.810
- Is that true, can you ?
- Oh, better be true.

06:32.852 --> 06:35.646
Otherwise, I'm stuck playing ditsy
coffee girl the rest of my life.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.857
Thank you.
Hon ? Thanks.

06:38.941 --> 06:43.153
Oh ! Hi, Nick. Hi.

06:43.236 --> 06:46.364
Oh, Lola, my love. When are you
gonna let me buy you dinner ?

06:46.447 --> 06:48.991
Nick, I don't know why you don't
believe me. I'm not your type.

06:49.075 --> 06:52.328
Trust me on this one. Cappuccino,
extra foam. Tall or grande ?

06:52.411 --> 06:55.372
Grande. Or at least
I like to think so.

06:55.456 --> 06:57.457
- Next.
- You know, rumor has it...

06:57.541 --> 07:00.001
I'm getting some really
big news at work today.

07:00.085 --> 07:02.921
At least come out with me.
Celebrate. I'll buy you a coffee.

07:03.004 --> 07:05.298
Memo to you:
I work in a coffee shop.

07:05.340 --> 07:07.300
Hi. What can I get you ?

07:07.342 --> 07:09.510
- Hi. I'll take--
- Want me to stop asking you out ?

07:09.594 --> 07:11.512
Sorry. This will
just take a sec.

07:11.595 --> 07:14.431
Because, Lola,
give me the word and I'll stop.

07:14.515 --> 07:18.060
Yes, I'm gonna give you the word
because I'm an actress.

07:18.143 --> 07:21.479
Or at least I'm trying to be one.
I'm trying to concentrate on that.

07:21.521 --> 07:24.649
So, you know, it would be
a good thing, if you wouldn't mind,

07:24.691 --> 07:26.651
to stop asking me out !

07:27.819 --> 07:29.946
Honey, you seem
so stressed.

07:30.029 --> 07:32.156
I am stressed.
I have a lot on my plate.

07:32.239 --> 07:34.199
So, let's not talk
about this now.

07:34.241 --> 07:36.535
Why don't I meet you here,
say, tomorrow ? 1 0:00 ? 1 0:30 ?

07:36.618 --> 07:38.620
- Okay, that would be good.
- So, that's a date ?

07:38.704 --> 07:41.998
It's a date.
Thank you.

07:42.040 --> 07:44.751
Sir,
that was inspiring.

07:44.834 --> 07:46.753
I know.

07:48.463 --> 07:50.381
[Woman]
Good morning, Sloane-Curtis.

07:50.464 --> 07:52.383
- Good morning, Mr. Marshall.
- Hi, honey.

07:52.466 --> 07:54.385
- What's the dirt ?
- I was at breakfast this morning--

07:54.468 --> 07:56.470
- Hey, Norm ! You winning ?
- Of course.

07:56.553 --> 07:59.389
I heard Miller's shopping around,
looking for a new agency.

07:59.431 --> 08:01.391
Miller Lite. I know.
I'm all over it.

08:01.433 --> 08:04.727
Also, I heard Darcy McGuire left
B.B.D. & O. Good morning, Angela.

08:04.811 --> 08:06.729
-You're kidding. Left or was fired ?
-I don't know.

08:06.813 --> 08:08.773
Everyone there
is thrilled to get rid of her.

08:08.856 --> 08:12.026
Well, so much for
edgy female vision.

08:12.068 --> 08:14.361
So, that girl we met
last night at the club,

08:14.403 --> 08:16.655
nothing happened after
you put her in the cab, right ?

08:16.738 --> 08:18.949
It did ?
Something happened ?

08:19.032 --> 08:21.034
But she said she had to
be in bed early.

08:21.117 --> 08:23.828
I had her in bed by 11:00.
Or was it quarter to ?

08:23.912 --> 08:25.830
You - You're like a genius,
you know that ?

08:25.914 --> 08:29.542
What can I tell you, buddy ? I'm
blessed. And today is my lucky day.

08:29.625 --> 08:33.712
Not only is my ex-wife remarrying--
right now, as a matter of fact--

08:33.796 --> 08:36.381
but Wanamaker called me himself,
wanted to see me first thing.

08:36.465 --> 08:39.051
- Called twice to confirm.
- Call me when he makes it official.

08:39.092 --> 08:43.013
It's not gonna be as easy to suck up
to ''creative director,'' you know.

08:43.096 --> 08:46.182
Not to worry. I'll make us a lunch
rez at the Drake to celebrate.

08:46.266 --> 08:49.602
Don't count your chickens,
huh ? 1:00 ?

08:49.685 --> 08:51.812
Pick you up.

08:51.896 --> 08:53.814
Can I borrow this ?

08:59.611 --> 09:01.613
- Hey, Dina.
- Hi.

09:01.696 --> 09:03.948
Do you know the difference
between a wife and a job ?

09:03.990 --> 09:06.284
- What is it ?
- After ten years, job still sucks.

09:06.326 --> 09:08.494
- [ Laughing ]
- That's a good one, huh ?

09:08.578 --> 09:11.789
I wouldn't do that if I were you.
That's not a good idea, no.

09:13.040 --> 09:14.959
- Oh, Mr. Marshall, hi.
- Hey.

09:15.042 --> 09:17.794
I put the storyboards on your desk.
Picked up your shoes from Barney's.

09:17.878 --> 09:19.796
Got your glasses fixed.
There was no charge.

09:19.880 --> 09:21.798
This morning's staff meeting
was cancelled.

09:21.882 --> 09:23.800
And I got your cigarettes.
They're next to your laptop.

09:23.883 --> 09:25.843
This morning's staff meeting
was cancelled.

09:25.927 --> 09:28.596
- That's what I was told.
- Hmm.

09:28.638 --> 09:32.725
Good morning, girls.
[ Chuckling ]

09:32.808 --> 09:35.019
Good afternoon, sire.

09:35.102 --> 09:38.063
Hey, anybody know why
the staff meeting was cancelled ?

09:38.146 --> 09:40.065
Nobody called us.

09:40.148 --> 09:42.942
Oh, but Mr. Wanamaker wants
to see you as soon as you get in,

09:42.984 --> 09:46.279
which I told his office
was 15 minutes ago.

09:46.321 --> 09:48.364
- I know.
- You couldn't show up on time ?

09:48.448 --> 09:51.575
You know you're being promoted.
But you look very sharp, by the way.

09:51.659 --> 09:53.577
- Thank you.
- Like a creative director.

09:53.661 --> 09:55.954
- Very distinguished.
- [ Exhales Deeply ]

09:55.996 --> 09:59.249
You able to handle yourselves
on the 44th floor ? Be truthful.

09:59.333 --> 10:01.710
Are you kidding ?
We were made for the 44th floor.

10:01.793 --> 10:04.796
Now, get up there already,
so we can break out the bubbly.

10:04.838 --> 10:07.256
- Don't wait up.
- [ Both ] Don't wait up.

10:07.340 --> 10:10.009
- He's so adorable.
- He says the cutest things.

10:12.511 --> 10:14.471
Boy.

10:16.265 --> 10:19.643
Sorry, buddy. I was in the board
meeting that would never end.

10:19.685 --> 10:21.895
- Have you been here long ?
- A couple minutes. That's all.

10:21.978 --> 10:24.314
Jess, can I get a cup of decaf
and a couple Tylenol?

10:24.355 --> 10:27.275
And see if we got any Echinacea.
And I need some club soda.

10:27.358 --> 10:31.487
I got something on my tie.
Know what ?Just get me another tie.

10:31.529 --> 10:35.824
I saw the mock-ups you did for
Johnny Walker. They're fantastic.

10:35.866 --> 10:38.118
Oh, that's my job, Dan.

10:38.201 --> 10:40.537
So, you know l'm not great
at making speeches,

10:40.620 --> 10:43.623
especially when I haven't
got you to write them for me.

10:43.707 --> 10:47.210
So, I'll do my best. I've been
in this racket over 30 years.

10:47.293 --> 10:49.337
Let me tell you something,
it doesn't get any easier.

10:49.420 --> 10:52.173
As a matter of fact,
it gets harder and harder.

10:52.214 --> 10:54.174
The '80s
were our glory days.

10:54.216 --> 10:57.261
They were all about
alcohol, tobacco and cars.

10:57.344 --> 10:59.846
I felt like
I was on top of my game.

10:59.888 --> 11:03.892
And then in the '90s, men stopped
dominating how dollars were spent,

11:03.975 --> 11:05.935
and we lost our compass.

11:06.019 --> 11:11.065
Women between 16 and 24 are
the fastest-growing consumer group.

11:11.148 --> 11:15.235
Girls who were born in the mid-'80s
control our advertising dollars.

11:15.319 --> 11:18.155
Sorry. No Echinacea.
Hi, Nick.

11:18.238 --> 11:20.782
- Hey.
- Red or lavender?

11:20.866 --> 11:23.660
Red. No, no, lavender.
That'sgood.

11:23.743 --> 11:27.413
Lavender's good. While we've been
shooting beer commercials...

11:27.497 --> 11:31.000
with the Swedish bikini team,
the industry has been transformed.

11:31.083 --> 11:33.919
We were the agency in town
ten years ago.

11:34.003 --> 11:36.797
Now we're struggling
to be third.

11:36.880 --> 11:39.883
lf we don't evolve and think
beyond our naturalability,

11:39.925 --> 11:42.510
we're gonna go down.

11:42.594 --> 11:46.431
''Think beyond our natural -''
I'm not quite clear what you mean.

11:46.514 --> 11:48.891
What do you know
about Darcy McGuire ?

11:48.933 --> 11:51.852
Oh, hey, l heard on the whisper
she just left B.B.D. & O.

11:51.936 --> 11:55.064
I never met the woman, but
I hear she's a real man-eater.

11:55.105 --> 11:57.691
She won that Cleo last year we
should have won for the add about--

11:57.774 --> 12:00.735
Oh, yeah, right.
That was her ? I forgot about that.

12:00.777 --> 12:06.199
Yeah, I wish I had. Oh, boy, I hear
she is a bitch on wheels.

12:06.282 --> 12:10.244
- That's very funny.
- Yeah, why ?

12:10.286 --> 12:13.122
[ Stammers ]
'Cause I just hired her.

12:14.290 --> 12:16.250
To do what ?

12:18.543 --> 12:22.047
You know I love you, Nick,
but it's a woman's world out there.

12:22.130 --> 12:25.633
Getting into a women's psyche
is not exactly your strong suit.

12:25.758 --> 12:27.969
You can get into their pants
better than anybody on Earth,

12:28.052 --> 12:30.012
but their psyche
is a whole other ball game.

12:30.054 --> 12:33.182
You hired Darcy McGuire
to do what ?

12:33.265 --> 12:37.186
She hasn't done it on her own yet,
but somebody was gonna grab her.

12:37.227 --> 12:40.480
And she's smart, Nick.
She's very smart.

12:40.564 --> 12:44.943
You made her creative director,
didn't you ?

12:45.026 --> 12:48.988
Sorry. This isn't easy, but I got
the board breathing down my neck.

12:49.030 --> 12:51.574
She's coming in this afternoon.
You'll meet her.

12:51.657 --> 12:53.993
- Come on. Roll with this.
- [ Coughs ]

12:54.034 --> 12:57.996
Work with her because she's got what
I need to keep this place afloat.

12:58.038 --> 13:00.916
She's got what you need,
meaning she's a woman.

13:00.999 --> 13:03.043
You know how we can
compete with that ?

13:07.422 --> 13:10.258
He's coming. He's coming.
He's coming.

13:10.341 --> 13:12.259
[ Women Scream ]

13:12.343 --> 13:15.721
Not so fast, girls.
Put it on ice.

13:17.055 --> 13:19.016
We'll break it out soon.

13:20.559 --> 13:22.686
We're not moving
to the 44th floor ?

13:22.727 --> 13:25.104
Not today.

13:26.689 --> 13:29.442
- Oh.
- Okay, Gigi, one more.

13:29.525 --> 13:33.112
Gigi, your ex is here.

13:39.868 --> 13:43.830
Honey, you look like...
$48 million.

13:43.913 --> 13:46.332
Thank you.

13:46.416 --> 13:48.459
- May I kiss the bride ?
- Sure.

13:50.836 --> 13:53.047
- Nick.
- Nick ! Ted.

13:53.088 --> 13:56.175
Congratulations, Ted.
You're a lucky man.

13:56.258 --> 13:58.218
Well, thanks.
I happen to agree.

13:58.302 --> 14:01.096
So, you're going on a cruise.
Two weeks, huh ?

14:01.179 --> 14:03.473
Well, actually, the cruise
is just the last week.

14:03.556 --> 14:05.767
Alexandra has an itinerary,
and I faxed one...

14:05.850 --> 14:08.061
to your office yesterday,
to your apartment last week.

14:08.102 --> 14:10.438
Ted's office has one,
as does the school.

14:10.521 --> 14:13.983
-In case I've fallen off the planet?
-You never know.

14:14.066 --> 14:16.568
[ Chuckles ]

14:16.610 --> 14:20.739
Hey, here she is. Pretty in pink.
So, two whole weeks together?

14:20.822 --> 14:23.783
- Yeah, how you gonna handle it ?
- l'm gonna love it.

14:23.825 --> 14:27.120
You can take care of your old man.
Cook for me. Get my slippers.

14:27.161 --> 14:30.248
- Yeah, that'll be happening.
- Alexandra has a boyfriend now.

14:30.331 --> 14:34.043
- Mom !
- So he won't be surprised.

14:34.126 --> 14:36.295
You have a boyfriend ?
You're only 13 years old.

14:36.378 --> 14:38.797
Am I ?
I thought I was 15.

14:38.880 --> 14:41.132
[ Chuckles ]
We're gonna be fiine.

14:42.217 --> 14:44.135
Look, I wanna meet Cameron.

14:44.219 --> 14:47.096
- Okay if I meet Dad at his place ?
- Is it all right ?

14:47.138 --> 14:49.098
- Yeah, well, I -
- What time ?

14:49.140 --> 14:51.267
8:00. 9:00, maybe ?

14:51.308 --> 14:53.352
- 7:30.
- Okay.

14:53.435 --> 14:56.438
- Bye, Mom.
- Oh, honey. I'm gonna miss you.

14:56.522 --> 14:59.524
I'm gonna miss you too.
Ted, have a good time.

14:59.608 --> 15:02.193
- Bye, pumpkin.
- Bye.

15:02.277 --> 15:04.946
- Nick.
- Honey.

15:04.988 --> 15:06.948
Later.

15:09.116 --> 15:12.703
Yeah, 7:30's fine.
Thanks for asking.

15:12.787 --> 15:15.456
And the name's Dad.

15:23.755 --> 15:25.673
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

15:28.134 --> 15:31.012
-Hey, I heard. I can't believe this.
-My next headache.

15:31.095 --> 15:33.013
Don't worry.
We'll get through it.

15:33.097 --> 15:35.015
Yeah.

15:35.099 --> 15:39.853
[ Laughing ] Everyone, everyone,
meet Darcy McGuire.

15:39.936 --> 15:41.813
- Oh, jeez.
- [ Applause ]

15:41.855 --> 15:45.358
- My goodness. Everybody showed up.
- Darcy, how are you ?

15:45.441 --> 15:48.319
- Nice to see you. Hi !
- Pleasant surprise.

15:48.361 --> 15:51.489
- God, what a small world.
- Welcome aboard.

15:51.572 --> 15:54.491
I'm so glad to meet you.

15:58.036 --> 16:00.247
Hello. I'm Darcy.

16:00.330 --> 16:02.707
Hi. I'm Nick Marshall.

16:02.791 --> 16:05.084
Oh, I've heard
a lot about you, Nick.

16:05.168 --> 16:08.337
-I've heard a lot about you too.
-Don't worry, can't all be true.

16:08.421 --> 16:11.173
