I swear.

01:45:48.794 --> 01:45:51.171
No, I'm not here because
you didn't show up for work.

01:45:51.254 --> 01:45:54.465
But I'm here--
Well, I--

01:45:54.549 --> 01:45:56.926
I bet you're wondering
why I am here, huh ?

01:45:58.135 --> 01:46:00.096
As a matter of fact,
I was just thinking that.

01:46:00.137 --> 01:46:04.224
I was thinking, ''Why is Mr. Marshall
here in my bedroom ?''

01:46:04.308 --> 01:46:07.728
You were...
thinking that just now ?

01:46:08.770 --> 01:46:10.689
Yeah, in my head.

01:46:10.772 --> 01:46:13.942
I must have water
in my ears or something.

01:46:13.983 --> 01:46:18.237
But you're, you know,
not thinking anything now, are you ?

01:46:19.322 --> 01:46:21.240
I'm thinking a million things.

01:46:21.323 --> 01:46:23.409
Really ?

01:46:23.492 --> 01:46:25.786
Because, you know,
usually I can, uh--

01:46:27.037 --> 01:46:29.498
I can, uh--

01:46:31.291 --> 01:46:33.293
You are thinking something
right this minute ?

01:46:33.376 --> 01:46:37.338
Mr. Marshall, I am thinking
that you are crazier than I am.

01:46:43.719 --> 01:46:45.888
I think--

01:46:45.971 --> 01:46:47.889
I think I lost--

01:46:50.642 --> 01:46:52.560
It's gone.

01:46:55.188 --> 01:46:57.106
I'm back.

01:46:58.357 --> 01:47:02.319
- I'm back.
- Mr. Marshall ?

01:47:02.403 --> 01:47:04.780
Yeah ?

01:47:04.863 --> 01:47:08.408
I'm sorry. Is there something
I can maybe do for you ?

01:47:10.702 --> 01:47:12.620
No.

01:47:13.705 --> 01:47:16.416
No, Erin, uh--

01:47:16.499 --> 01:47:19.377
Actually, I came here to see if
I could do something for you.

01:47:21.378 --> 01:47:23.589
- For me ?
- Yeah.

01:47:24.923 --> 01:47:26.883
See, the truth is--

01:47:28.385 --> 01:47:30.303
The truth--

01:47:32.472 --> 01:47:35.183
Erin, the truth is,

01:47:35.266 --> 01:47:39.353
I'm glad I got here before you
did anything to hurt yourself.

01:47:43.857 --> 01:47:45.984
What makes you think that
I would, uh,

01:47:46.068 --> 01:47:49.029
do something
to hurt myself?

01:47:50.196 --> 01:47:52.115
I just sensed it.

01:47:54.242 --> 01:47:56.160
Really ?

01:47:57.286 --> 01:47:59.246
You could sense that ?

01:48:05.043 --> 01:48:07.546
Well, that's not--
That's not good.

01:48:08.755 --> 01:48:11.049
[Sobbing]

01:48:11.132 --> 01:48:15.345
Yeah. But the real reason
I'm here is because--

01:48:15.428 --> 01:48:18.264
Well, here's the thing. The real
reason I'm here is because--

01:48:18.306 --> 01:48:20.266
As you know
we have the Nike account,

01:48:20.349 --> 01:48:22.351
and we have a job opening
in our team.

01:48:22.434 --> 01:48:25.687
And Darcy McGuire and I,
we were just discussing--

01:48:25.771 --> 01:48:28.857
really spitballing on who could be
great enough to fill that void.

01:48:28.940 --> 01:48:31.067
Suddenly, your name popped
into my head, and I remembered...

01:48:31.109 --> 01:48:33.528
that you once applied
for a job as a copywriter.

01:48:33.611 --> 01:48:37.156
I thought I'd come down here and
see if you were still interested.

01:48:37.240 --> 01:48:39.575
Didn't you try and meet with me
a while back ?

01:48:39.617 --> 01:48:44.163
Yeah, I tried, but you were
unavailable, and then out of town--

01:48:44.246 --> 01:48:46.164
Well, now I'm available.

01:48:46.248 --> 01:48:49.084
And as you can plainly see
I'm in town,

01:48:49.126 --> 01:48:51.336
so I'm here
to take that meeting...

01:48:51.419 --> 01:48:53.254
if you're available.

01:48:56.716 --> 01:48:58.926
I'm available.

01:48:58.968 --> 01:49:01.554
I'm unbelievably available.

01:49:07.809 --> 01:49:09.769
[ Buzzing ]

01:49:18.819 --> 01:49:21.113
[Dialing]

01:49:22.615 --> 01:49:24.825
[ Ringing ]

01:49:30.455 --> 01:49:32.373
[Darcy On Answering Machine]
Hi, this is Darcy McGuire.

01:49:32.457 --> 01:49:34.584
l'm not home right now,
so please leave a message.

01:49:34.667 --> 01:49:38.796
- I'll get back as soon as I can.
- [Beeps]

01:49:38.879 --> 01:49:41.257
Darcy ?
Hi, Darcy, it's Nick.

01:49:41.340 --> 01:49:43.717
Uh, l'm standing right outside
your place here.

01:49:43.801 --> 01:49:46.220
I sure wish I could find you,
get a hold of you.

01:49:46.303 --> 01:49:48.472
Are you all right ?
I hope so.

01:49:48.555 --> 01:49:50.890
Anyway, call me
when you get this.

01:49:50.974 --> 01:49:54.310
I'm on my cell.
Triple five, 1-2-2-6.

01:49:54.352 --> 01:49:56.521
I really need to talk to you.

01:49:56.604 --> 01:49:59.065
Uh--

01:49:59.148 --> 01:50:01.233
Just making sure
you're not there.

01:50:01.317 --> 01:50:04.111
You're not, right ?
No, I didn't think so.

01:50:04.194 --> 01:50:07.114
All right, so call me, please.
Please.

01:50:07.197 --> 01:50:09.116
Bye.

01:50:31.845 --> 01:50:34.722
[Cell Phone Ringing]

01:50:34.806 --> 01:50:37.016
- Darcy ?
- [ Gigi ] No, it's me.

01:50:37.099 --> 01:50:40.144
Gigi ? Uh--
Is everything all right ?

01:50:40.227 --> 01:50:42.813
- Are you back in town already ?
- No, not until tomorrow.

01:50:42.896 --> 01:50:46.316
Alex called me three times
from a pay phone really upset.

01:50:46.400 --> 01:50:49.694
Then we got disconnected. What's
the matter ? Isn't she at the prom ?

01:50:50.862 --> 01:50:52.864
[ Sighs ]
The prom.

01:51:15.718 --> 01:51:18.179
Excuse me. Do you know
where Alex Marshall is ?

01:51:18.262 --> 01:51:20.389
Little tenth grader ?
Brown hair ? About this high ?

01:51:20.473 --> 01:51:23.225
I saw her in the ladies' room.
She's been there for, like, an hour.

01:51:28.772 --> 01:51:31.316
Alex, are you in here ?

01:51:31.399 --> 01:51:33.318
[Alex Sobbing]

01:51:35.570 --> 01:51:37.488
Alex, it's me.

01:51:37.572 --> 01:51:39.490
[Scoffs]
What are you doing here ?

01:51:39.573 --> 01:51:41.909
Oh, honey, I just--

01:51:41.951 --> 01:51:43.911
You know, I can't believe
that I screwed up.

01:51:43.952 --> 01:51:45.913
I wasn't there when
you left for the prom.

01:51:45.954 --> 01:51:50.166
Yeah, well, that's not why l'm
in here, so you can just go, okay ?

01:51:50.250 --> 01:51:53.211
Oh, boy, I feel awful.
Are you okay ? I mean, I--

01:51:53.294 --> 01:51:55.296
Come on out. Let me see
how you look, at least.

01:51:55.380 --> 01:51:58.382
- Come on.
- [Sobbing]I look like crap !

01:51:58.466 --> 01:52:01.802
I already took my hair out
and everything.

01:52:06.890 --> 01:52:08.850
So, you know,
what happened ?

01:52:10.727 --> 01:52:12.896
Well, if I told you,
you'd just freak out, so--

01:52:14.981 --> 01:52:16.941
What have you got to lose ?
Try me.

01:52:18.818 --> 01:52:21.320
Okay.

01:52:21.403 --> 01:52:25.657
Cameron and his friends,
they had this big plan.

01:52:25.741 --> 01:52:29.870
They rented this hotelroom
and-and--

01:52:31.371 --> 01:52:33.289
It was like a suite.

01:52:34.457 --> 01:52:38.211
Basically, I promised him
that I was gonna--

01:52:39.795 --> 01:52:42.047
I can't believe I'm gonna
say this to you. [Sniffles]

01:52:43.257 --> 01:52:46.176
I promised him that
I was gonna...

01:52:46.260 --> 01:52:48.178
sleep with him
after the prom.

01:52:51.765 --> 01:52:53.766
And like an hour ago,

01:52:53.850 --> 01:52:56.185
we were on the dance floor
and I said,

01:52:56.269 --> 01:52:59.230
''I'm sorry, Cameron.
You know, I'm just not ready.''

01:52:59.271 --> 01:53:01.357
Good.
Good girl.

01:53:01.440 --> 01:53:04.109
- Dad, come on !
- l'm sorry, l'm sorry. Go on.

01:53:04.193 --> 01:53:06.236
Then he goes, ''Well, the limo,
the room and the tux,

01:53:06.320 --> 01:53:09.906
it all cost me 400 bucks. ''

01:53:09.948 --> 01:53:12.075
And I said,
''I'm sorry. I'm just not--''

01:53:12.117 --> 01:53:16.245
And he cuts me off
and he says,

01:53:16.329 --> 01:53:21.917
''I never should've asked a sophomore
to the prom. What a waste.''

01:53:23.877 --> 01:53:26.088
Then two seconds later,

01:53:26.129 --> 01:53:29.090
he goes and meets up
with his old girlfriend...

01:53:29.132 --> 01:53:31.801
and starts making out
with her.

01:53:31.885 --> 01:53:34.262
I mean, this disgusting slut
with a tongue ring.

01:53:34.304 --> 01:53:37.932
And then they were
laughing and--

01:53:37.974 --> 01:53:39.934
I just can't
go out there ever.

01:53:39.975 --> 01:53:42.269
- Oh, honey, l'm so proud of you.
- Dad !

01:53:42.311 --> 01:53:44.897
- What are you doing ?
- I'm sorry. I'm-I'm sorry.

01:53:44.980 --> 01:53:48.442
But I am.
And believe it or not,

01:53:48.525 --> 01:53:50.819
I know what it's like
to be a woman.

01:53:50.902 --> 01:53:55.114
I mean, it's not
as easy as it looks.

01:53:55.198 --> 01:53:59.076
You stood up for yourself. You know
how ahead of the game you are ?

01:53:59.160 --> 01:54:02.621
Anyway, a guy that treats you like
that and talks to you like that,

01:54:02.705 --> 01:54:05.165
- he's not--
- Worth my time. Yes, I know.

01:54:05.207 --> 01:54:09.169
- It's true. He's not.
- He's a gameplayer, I hate that.

01:54:12.547 --> 01:54:15.800
You are so much smarter
than me.

01:54:22.723 --> 01:54:25.475
And look at you.

01:54:25.517 --> 01:54:28.812
That clown made out with a girl
with a tongue ring over you ?

01:54:31.898 --> 01:54:34.651
Honey...

01:54:34.692 --> 01:54:36.944
you look beautiful.

01:54:39.864 --> 01:54:42.783
Thanks.

01:54:48.121 --> 01:54:50.040
Take me home, Dad.

01:55:44.631 --> 01:55:47.467
What am I doing ?
She's not in the refrigerator.

01:56:03.982 --> 01:56:06.443
I wonder if it's too late
to go over there.

01:56:06.526 --> 01:56:09.738
No, it's not too late. It's never
too late to do the right thing.

01:56:09.779 --> 01:56:13.783
That's what I'll do. I'll go over
there and I'll do the right thing.

01:56:18.454 --> 01:56:20.456
[lntercom Buzzing]

01:56:25.294 --> 01:56:27.212
Hello ?

01:56:27.295 --> 01:56:29.881
Uh, hi, it's me.
Oh, I'm glad I found you.

01:56:29.965 --> 01:56:31.800
Uh--

01:56:31.883 --> 01:56:33.927
Can I come up ?

01:56:35.970 --> 01:56:38.472
Darcy ?
I need to--

01:56:38.556 --> 01:56:41.100
[Door Buzzing]

01:56:43.018 --> 01:56:44.978
Hey.

01:56:45.020 --> 01:56:47.272
You need to what ?
It's 1:00 in the morning.

01:56:47.356 --> 01:56:49.816
I need to talk to you.

01:56:49.900 --> 01:56:51.568
Okay.

01:56:53.695 --> 01:56:55.655
Thanks.

01:56:58.699 --> 01:57:00.993
So, you sleep here now ?

01:57:01.076 --> 01:57:04.371
I thought I might as well give it a
try before I have to sell the place.

01:57:04.455 --> 01:57:06.373
Sell it? You're not
selling the place.

01:57:06.456 --> 01:57:08.583
Can't afford to keep it.
I don't have a job.

01:57:08.667 --> 01:57:12.170
You know, you ought to try
returning some of your phone calls.

01:57:12.253 --> 01:57:15.006
- You got your job back.
- Oh, do I ?

01:57:15.089 --> 01:57:17.592
- You're a riot. You know that ?
- lt's true.

01:57:17.675 --> 01:57:19.677
Dan told me so himself.

01:57:19.760 --> 01:57:22.972
Why would he tell you that ? I
didn't do the job he hired me to do.

01:57:23.055 --> 01:57:25.015
Even I don't blame him
for firing me.

01:57:25.057 --> 01:57:28.310
Look, I'm, uh--
You can come on in.

01:57:28.351 --> 01:57:30.353
I don't have any chairs,
but if you wanna--

01:57:30.437 --> 01:57:32.480
What if I told you that...

01:57:32.564 --> 01:57:34.607
you did everything
that you were hired to do--

01:57:34.691 --> 01:57:38.945
everything-- but that
someone was sabotaging you ?

01:57:40.321 --> 01:57:44.158
Picking your brain,
swiping your ideas and--

01:57:44.199 --> 01:57:48.453
Well, you-- you never
even knew what hit you.

01:57:48.537 --> 01:57:51.915
- How is that possible ?
- Oh, trust me, it's possible.

01:57:51.998 --> 01:57:53.833
Well, who would do
such an awful thing ?

01:57:57.044 --> 01:57:59.463
I would.

01:58:02.549 --> 01:58:04.760
I was a dope
with a corner office.

01:58:04.843 --> 01:58:09.222
And when you came with the job
I was supposed to have,

01:58:09.306 --> 01:58:13.017
I mean, it didn't matter
to me that...

01:58:13.059 --> 01:58:16.437
you were better at it than me
or you earned it more than I did.

01:58:16.521 --> 01:58:21.400
As far as I was concerned, it was
mine, and I was gonna get it back.

01:58:21.442 --> 01:58:25.404
So I took advantage of you
in the worst possible way.

01:58:28.990 --> 01:58:30.909
Have you ever done that ?

01:58:30.992 --> 01:58:34.537
Taken the wrong road and--
No, of course you haven't.

01:58:34.621 --> 01:58:38.040
You wouldn't do that.
That's just--

01:58:38.082 --> 01:58:40.292
Somebody like me does that.

01:58:40.376 --> 01:58:43.087
And, uh--

01:58:43.170 --> 01:58:47.090
The problem with that was that while
I was digging the hole under you...

01:58:49.467 --> 01:58:51.553
I found out
all about you.

01:58:51.594 --> 01:58:53.555
And the more I found out...

01:58:54.681 --> 01:58:56.599
the more you dazzled me.

01:58:58.684 --> 01:59:02.896
I mean, shook my world,
changed my life, dazzled me.

01:59:04.940 --> 01:59:08.026
And guys like that ex-husband
of yours, he made you feel that...

01:59:09.194 --> 01:59:12.697
the price you pay
just for being you...

01:59:12.781 --> 01:59:14.907
is that you don't get
to have love.

01:59:14.949 --> 01:59:17.493
Isn't that what you were
trying to say the other night ?

01:59:17.577 --> 01:59:22.414
That you weren't complete ?
That you weren't really a winner ?

01:59:23.791 --> 01:59:25.751
Everything about you--

01:59:25.792 --> 01:59:29.087
how smart you are,
how good you are--

01:59:29.171 --> 01:59:32.257
everything just makes me
want you even more.

01:59:37.094 --> 01:59:39.847
Oh, wow.
Boy.

01:59:39.930 --> 01:59:42.016
So it looks like I'm here
at 1:00 in the morning...

01:59:42.099 --> 01:59:46.019
being all heroic
trying to rescue you,

01:59:46.103 --> 01:59:48.772
but the truth is...

01:59:48.814 --> 01:59:51.232
I'm the one that needs
to be rescued here.

01:59:58.656 --> 02:00:00.658
I sure wish
I could read your mind.

02:00:08.165 --> 02:00:11.793
Well, I was thinking that, um,

02:00:11.835 --> 02:00:15.963
if everything you're saying
is true,

02:00:16.005 --> 02:00:18.132
if I really have
my job back...

02:00:24.096 --> 02:00:26.014
then I think you're fired.

02:00:30.852 --> 02:00:33.938
Well, I never-- I never really
thought about it from that angle.

02:00:37.108 --> 02:00:40.986
Well, not that
I don't deserve it. I-do-do--

02:00:41.028 --> 02:00:42.988
I'm stuttering.

02:00:56.542 --> 02:00:58.669
Now I feel kind of, uh,

02:00:58.753 --> 02:01:01.505
embarrassed that I told you
I needed to be rescued.

02:01:02.715 --> 02:01:05.425
But that's-that's fine.

02:01:19.522 --> 02:01:22.024
That's it ?

02:01:27.237 --> 02:01:29.406
I don't want that to be it.

02:01:29.489 --> 02:01:31.700
I don't want that
to be it at all.

02:01:31.783 --> 02:01:36.037
Then don't let a little thing like
me firing you stand in your way.

02:01:40.374 --> 02:01:43.919
I didn't know
what to react to first.

02:01:44.002 --> 02:01:46.046
Hey, news flash.

02:01:46.088 --> 02:01:48.048
I took the wrong road.

02:01:50.091 --> 02:01:52.594
What kind of knight
in shining armor would I be...

02:01:52.677 --> 02:01:55.680
if the man I love
needs rescuing...

02:01:55.763 --> 02:01:58.349
and I just let him
walk out my door ?

02:02:06.481 --> 02:02:08.442
My hero.

